      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The cholesterol-lowering agents called <i>statins</i>, such as simvastatin (Zocor) and pravastatin (Pravachol), are among the most widely prescribed drugs in the world, with annual sales estimated at approximately $25 billion. Identify the functional groups in both, and tell how the two substances differ.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdndRIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--b238dc1d56ebdee6529553b1093c0b3686d6a2b9/OChem_03_EC_008.jpg\" alt=\"The chemical structures of simvastatin and pravastatin are represented.\">",
